OL,3,CWorkers deaths 'should never have
OL,4,Chappened' says Network Rail
OL,6,FThe families of two rail workers who
OL,7,Fdied after being hit by a train near
OL,8,FMargam, Port Talbot have paid tribute
OL,9,Fto "devoted family members, cherished
OL,10,Ffriends, and valued members of their
OL,11,Fcommunity."
OL,13,FGareth Delbridge, 64, from Kenfig Hill
OL,14,Fand Michael Lewis, 58, from North
OL,15,FCornelly were part of a team carrying
OL,16,Fout maintenance on the tracks between
OL,17,FPort Talbot and Bridgend on 3 July
OL,18,F2019 when they were fatally struck.
