OL,3,CWorkers deaths 'should never have
OL,4,Chappened' says Network Rail
OL,6,FNetwork Rail has said since the
OL,7,Ftragedy, it has continued to
OL,8,F"transform the safety of its workforce
OL,9,Fthrough the development of new
OL,10,Ftechnology and planning tools,"
OL,11,Feliminating the need for staff to work
OL,12,Fon the railway when trains are running.
OL,14,FIt says it's already committed #70
OL,15,Fmillion of investment to track worker
OL,16,Fsafety initiatives, and has invested a
OL,17,Ftotal of more than #300 million to
OL,18,Fdeliver an "unprecedented" level of
OL,19,Freform to working practices.
